This paper deals with image translation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed mix and match networks involve multiple encoders and decoders, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders and side information, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also involves the alignment of encoder-decoder pairs, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with cross-modal image translation, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
